article.headline: LSU 68, Nicholls St. 56
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Tasmin Mitchell scored a season-high 19 points and LSU remained unbeaten with a 68-56 victory against Nicholls State on Wednesday night. Mitchell, who scored 16 in the second half, led four LSU players in double figures as Bo Spencer and Marcus Thornton had 17 points each and Garrett Temple scored a season-high 10. Anatoly Bose was the Colonels' (6-4) leading scorer with 14 points. Ryan Bathie had 13 points for Nicholls State, saw its five-game winning streak end. Fred Hunter, the Colonels' top scorer, was held to four points -- 11 below his average. The Tigers, who have opened the season with eight victories for the first time in five seasons, came back from a seven-point deficit to post the win. LSU did not take a comfortable lead until the final eight minutes.
